The room itself was standard; clean, not particularly spacious, shower only, working TV, toiletries, coffee and free internet.	If you want to spend all day in a bigger room go and stay at a bog-standard chain hotel and pay twice the price.	The service was perfect and the price, for some reason, is much better than many of the chain hotels in the area.	My room was a basic Club Quarters room - standard amenities.	When we go away it's usually to a place with deluxe accomodations to relax & rejuvenate from our hectic lives & this is not up to my standards.